%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
% Adjustable language mode settings.
%
% Changing the language context will change the guide words for chart
% titles (graphs, tables); article structure words, such as the `table 
% of contents', `references', etc.; and the guide words in the theorem
% environment, such as `theorem', `lemma', etc.
%
% Considering the font size and styles of the abstract title and the
% chapter/section numbers are not only different in different language 
% modes of these three document classes, but also different in these three
% document classes themselves, this part of formatting is seperated into
% six style package files under the directory `customized_headers` and the
% `customized_abstract`.
%
% See the following files for the adjustable language mode settings for
% the abstract title and chapter/section numbers of the three document
% classes:
%
%   [1]: ./tex/latex/uglylatex/customized_abstract/abstractblock.sty
%   [2]: ./tex/latex/uglylatex/customized_abstract/abstractpage.sty
%   [3]: ./tex/latex/uglylatex/customized_abstract/runinabstract.sty
%   [4]: ./tex/latex/uglylatex/customized_headers/noteheaders.sty
%   [5]: ./tex/latex/uglylatex/customized_headers/paperheaders.sty
%   [6]: ./tex/latex/uglylatex/customized_headers/repheaders.sty
%

